Roxy is a 6 year old giant schnauzer!  She is such a sweet girl who just loves everyone and loves attention.  If you're home, she wants to be near you.  She is on medication for arthritis, which isn't surprising given her size.

Applications may be submitted at hbschnauzerrescue.com

Dogs will only be adopted to residents of the following: Delaware, Maryland, New Jersey, Pennsylvania, Virginia, West Virginia and DC.  

Adopters must agree to take the dog through obedience training within 3 months of adoption (unless the dog is over age 10).  

Adopters must agree to keep the dog current on vaccinations and heart worm, flea, tick prevention on a year round basis.

Abbey is on her way to Minnesota this weekend.  She is about 4 years old.  She is dog friendly.  Please email adoptions.protectingpaws@gmail.com for more information or for an application for adoption.

Hey Yall! My name is Cobraâ¦â¦â¦yep itâs a tough name, but I am a big bundle of loveâ¦â¦.my foster dad is a helicopter pilot so my brothers and sisters all have helicopter names ! #flyarmyâ¦â¦â¦..anywayâ¦â¦back to meâ¦â¦â¦I am a fine looking pup! I am gonna be a really big boy according to our vet.  I am the second largest in our litter and I am close on the tail of my brother Huey!  We have no clue what we are other than FABULOUS! Right now the vet is calling us a Louisiana Love Mixâ¦â¦. A little terrier, a little curâ¦â¦â¦a dash of labâ¦â¦.maybe a dash of schnauzerâ¦â¦we donât knowâ¦â¦..We were left abandoned in a house and our foster mom got us the first day so we didnât go without at all.  Our vet seems to think we will be upwards of 75 lbs full grown and is currently 38 lbs as of March 15 2018.  My feet are HUGEâ¦â¦We are estimated to be born around the first week of November 2017.  My weight right now is about 33 lbs.  I am growing fast.  I get along well with my sisters and have a few tussles with my brother at times.  I get along well with my foster brother Flash who is a hound, my foster brother Peanut who is a lab and my super dominant foster sister Dottie who is a pitt mix.  I love everyone, however I am very fast and I love very hardâ¦â¦.I would probably do better with an older child that I couldnât knock down.  I have been around a toddler and I love her, but I am a little too exuberant for her.  I love to swim in our pondâ¦fight with a stickâ¦.chase a ballâ¦...run in circles with my family and have a great time.  I do better with a harness right now.  With some love and training not only will I be the best looking dog everâ¦â¦â¦..I will love you forever and then some.  Please consider adopting me.  If you want to learn more about meâ¦â¦.just askâ¦â¦.the lovely adoption ladies know my foster mom really well and they will hook you up with the âCobra Hotlineâ of information! I am ready to head north!!!

Our adoption fees are:  Puppies - Adults $ 525, Seniors $325.  These adoption rates include transport to designated New England pick up locations using either Rescue Road Trips or Pets LLC.   If you do a search you will see that this is a very reasonable adoption fee and comparable to other rescues. 

All our dogs are altered (spayed or neutered), DHLPP, rabies, Heartworm tested and neg, microchipped and get a fecal and treated for parasites if any found. A meet and greet is not possible before adoption unless we have a foster home open up. Most times our dogs get adopted before a foster home becomes available - and if so they go straight to adoption. Foster mom's talk to adopters and feel confident that this will be a match before our dogs are transported up. Also if by some chance it is not a match we have a safety net in place as we ask that adopters let us know that it is not a match and we direct you to take the dog to a foster home or boarding kennel once that is arranged. If necessary, we might ask you to foster the dog until a foster home can be arranged.  One of our transport companies, Rescue Road Trips, was featured on The Today Show - view it at http://www.today.com/video/today/55034556#55034556

If you are a Massachusetts or New Hampshire residence additional fees apply  due to State quarantine requirements.  

We hope to help make a difference in a rescue dogs life into loving responsible homes.

Rocco came to us from a Southern California humane society.  He has been in a foster home since arriving. He is doing well there and his foster said, "Hello, My name is Rocco, and I'm looking for a forever home. I'm two years old and my foster brother is helping me remember all the things I already knew. I'm learning real fast what I can't do around here. I'm housebroken and good on a leash. If you want me to play with children, make sure they are old enough to be smarter than me, (and I'm pretty smart). I like to cuddle, but I like to explore, I'm so smart I know how to sit and lay down (doesn't take a rocket scientist). I like my foster home but I know there's a way out, give me time. I have some trust issues, but I'm pretty sure I'll stick around any forever home that likes to play a lot."

Rocco does not like to be examined at a vet's office, so that will take some planning.  But in a home, he is great.  

Please EMAIL only about adopting him. Email us at phxgsrescue@hotmail.com

Rocco's adoption fee is $225. If you are interested in this dog, please email us phxgsrescue@hotmail.com Email is always answered more quickly than phone calls are returned. Thank you for taking the time to email us.

phxgsrescue@hotmail.com

Applications in the immediate area are given preference and you need to be within a day's driving distance to come and pick up a dog. We do not ship our dogs. When you adopt a dog from us and for some reason it doesn't work, the dog be returned to VSGSR and a full refund is given with in the first thirty days. Any dog adopted from us at any time comes back to Valley of the Sun Giant Schnauzer Rescue if the adopter can not keep the dog. We are responsible for our dogs for their lifetime. And we hope our adopters are also. Each dog will have been neutered, had full panel blood tests done, been microchipped and up to date on all of his shots. We do prefer that you be within driving distance of Phoenix to adopt one of our dogs. If the adoption doesn't work out for some reason with in the first thirty days, the adoption fee is refunded upon return of the dog. Our contract states that during the life of the dog, should something happen that you can not keep any of our dogs, the dog must be returned to VSGSR. Should a family member wish to adopt the dog, they would be given first priority. We are responsible for our dogs for their entire life. If interested, please email us at phxgsrescue@hotmail.com for more information. Emailing is the best way to contact us as we are all volunteers.

Theo pronounced Ta-o has arrived.  He  has a lot to learn but in a patient home who knows giants, he will blossom. He has never been around other animals and was described as very dominant by the trainer who surrendered him to us. he stressed that Theo is very dominant. So far he is just a classic giant schnauzer. But he is  not for the feint of heart or quick tempered human. This guy needs constant training and exercise, exercise, and more exercise. He lived outside for sometime now so will need to learn house manners.  He is NOT for a family with children  as he does not know not to jump. 

He can and will learn with patience.  He just arrived on March 2 and will need to be neutered and he will also be groomed and get vet checked.  He is up to date on his shots. 

He lived with a family who had no idea about giant schnauzers and could not deal with him so he was sent to live outside.  He was just two years old in October so  he is a typical young male giant schnauzer that needs constant and consistent training. He is not and never will be a couch potato.  If you are not an active person or family, this is not the dog for you. You must enjoy a challenge and exercise and working with your dog on a daily basis.

Catherine is about 7 pounds of wiggles and love, she is happy and friendly and  gets along with all other animals.  She will make a wonderful addition to any family.  She is bonded with JR the father of her  litters before being surrendered to the Sanctuary they are very much a bonded pair and it would be great if they could be placed together.

Archie is around 3 years old and weighs 9-10 pounds.  He looks a lot bigger because of all the hair.  He's a very affectionate dog, gets along with people well.  He's very sweet and loving.  We have no idea what breed he is, but he's beautiful in person.  He is very animated and active.  Archie needs to be with a strong, experienced owner.  A home with fewer distractions would be just fine for him. He would do well as an only dog, or with a playmate about the same size.  A fenced-in yard is required.

FOSTER HOMES NEEDED!
Brussels Griffon & Affenpinscher â¢ Adult â¢ Male/Female â¢ Small
Spayed/Neutered â¢ Current on vaccinations â¢ Prefers a home without: Young Children
 
American Brussels Griffon Rescue Alliance (ABGRA) & American Affenpinscher Rescue (AAR) needs more volunteers to fulfill our mission to rescue, rehabilitate and find loving forever homes for dogs in need.

We primarily focus on rescuing Brussels Griffons, Affenpinschers and mixes of these toy breeds. ABGRAâs rescued Griffs and Affens come from shelters, breeders and owner surrenders. 

ABGRA currently needs foster homes in the Midwest and on the West Coast, especially in Arkansas, Kansas, Missouri, Illinois, Iowa, and Southern California.  If you are an adult over 25 years old, work from home, do not have young children, have a securely fenced yard, have experience with dogs and can offer your time and love for Griffs and Affens in need, you may qualify to be a foster home! 

Many of our Griffs and Affens are rescued in the Lower Midwest, so they also need transport to our foster homes in other areas.  We are a charitable 501c3 organization, so fuel to transport these dogs is tax deductible to the extent allowed by law, as are monetary donations.

Please go to our website, www.abgra.org.  You will find more information there and our foster home application, which is required for fostering and/or transporting.  If you cannot volunteer, but would still like to help, tax deductible monetary donations for veterinary care are always needed too!  ABGRA provides complete veterinary care for our rescued dogs, including spay/neuter, vaccinations, heart worm tests/preventative and other vet care as needed.

Please join with us to help rescued Griffs and Affens become healthy, happy dogs, enabling them to find their forever, loving homes.  You will discover that nurturing and rehabilitating these precious little dogs will be one of the most rewarding experiences of your life!
He has a terrier personality.  He loves people.  Please text 513 383 0202 for more information.
